📘 Project Overview and Scenario
This Digital Literacy project is designed to develop awareness and practical understanding of responsible and safe
use of digital technologies among students. The project is based on the scenario of a student acting as a “Digital
Ambassador,” whose role is to guide peers in navigating the digital world effectively and securely.
Through a series of structured tasks, the project covers important aspects of digital literacy, including online safety, 
phishing and UPI fraud awareness, responsible social media usage, digital communication etiquette, and the use of modern
tools such as Google Forms, Canva, GitHub, and HackerRank. Each task focuses on building both theoretical knowledge and
practical skills, such as creating quizzes, designing infographics, writing professional emails, and analysing real-world cybercrime cases.


The overall objective of this project is to equip students with essential digital skills, promote safe online behavior,
and prepare them for academic, professional, and everyday digital interactions in an increasingly technology-driven world.
For this project, I used Canva as my primary design tool and GitHub for organizing and submitting my work. Canva helped me
create a clean, structured, and visually appealing infographic using its wide range of templates, icons, and design elements
. The design, titled “The Digital Student’s Handbook: Navigating Your Campus Life Online,” focuses on guiding first-year students 
toward digital success. It presents key concepts such as building a professional digital identity, communicating safely and effectively,
and understanding digital literacy. The infographic also highlights essential tools like Canva, GitHub, and LinkedIn, along with important 
practices such as writing professional emails, maintaining a minimalist online presence, and recognizing cyber threats like phishing and UPI
fraud. Additionally, it includes information about reporting cybercrime through official channels.
One of the most interesting aspects of this project was learning how digital literacy plays a crucial role in 
academic and professional life. It goes beyond basic technology use and includes communication, safety, and personal branding. The most
challenging part was organizing multiple ideas into a balanced layout while keeping the design visually engaging and easy to understand.
Overall, this project improved both my technical awareness and creative design skills.
 

